---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Westbrook Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Westbrook Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Understanding the cannabis business landscape in Westbrook, Maine. Local ordinances, medical dispensary rules, and cultivation opportunities."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Westbrook Cannabis Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating the cannabis market in Westbrook, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Regulatory Notice: Retail Prohibition" type="tip">
      As of March 2026, **Westbrook does not permit adult-use (recreational) retail marijuana stores.** While the city has opted into other categories of the cannabis industry, entrepreneurs looking to open a recreational storefront should look toward neighboring communities like <a href="/guides/portland-dispensary-guide/">Portland</a> or <a href="/guides/south-portland-dispensary-guide/">South Portland</a>.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Westbrook remains an important player in the Maine cannabis industry, but its local approach differs significantly from its neighbors. While recreational retail is prohibited, the city has maintained a path for medical cannabis dispensaries and caregiver operations. Located just west of Portland, Westbrook offers a more industrial and manufacturing-focused landscape for the "back-end" of the cannabis supply chain.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Industrial Potential" type="passion">
      Westbrook's strength lies in its industrial heritage. For those looking to build cultivation or manufacturing hubs, the city's mill spaces and commercial zones offer robust infrastructure that is often more affordable than Portland proper.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Current Status: What is Allowed?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Medical Dispensaries</strong> - Westbrook continues to allow licensed medical cannabis operations.</li>
        <li><strong>Caregiver Operations</strong> - Small-scale medical cultivation is permitted under state and local rules.</li>
        <li><strong>Recreational Retail</strong> - ❌ **PROHIBITED.** Local ordinances currently block recreational storefronts.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Westbrook Market Analysis</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>32,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Retail Opt-In</td><td>No (Adult-Use Retail Prohibited)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Medical Opt-In</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Industrial Space</td><td>High availability in mill districts</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 25</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Success Tips for Westbrook</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Focus on the **Medical Market** if you are looking for patient-facing retail.</li>
        <li>Consider Westbrook for **Cultivation or Warehousing** due to lower real estate costs.</li>
        <li>Stay engaged with city council meetings; municipal "opt-in" statuses can change via local vote.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.westbrookmaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">City of Westbrook Official Site</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only. Local ordinances are subject to change. Verify Westbrook's current "Opt-In" status with the City Clerk's office.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
